Ocala.West Ocala Historic District: The West Ocala Historic District is a historic district in Ocala, Florida. It is roughly bounded by Northwest 4th Street, West Silver Springs Boulevard, and Northwest 12th Avenue, encompasses approximately 350 acres (1.4 km2), and contains 104 historic buildings. On June 27, 2002, it was added to the U.S. National Register of Historic Places.
